& =\frac{281(49-18 \sin \theta \cos \theta+i(21 \cos \theta+42 \sin \theta))}{49+9 \cos ^2 \theta}
\end{aligned}
$$
<br/><br/>For positive integer
<br/><br/>$$
\begin{aligned}
& \operatorname{Im}(A)=0 \\\\
& 21 \cos \theta+42 \sin \theta=0 \\\\
& \tan \theta=\frac{-1}{2} ; \sin 2 \theta=\frac{-4}{5}, \cos ^2 \theta=\frac{4}{5}
\end{aligned}
$$
<br/><br/>$$
\begin{aligned}
& \operatorname{Re}(\mathrm{A})=\frac{281(49-9 \sin 2 \theta)}{49+9 \cos ^2 \theta} \\\\
& =\frac{281\left(49-9 \times \frac{-4}{5}\right)}{49+9 \times \frac{4}{5}}=281(+ \text { ve integer })
\end{aligned}
$$

